body:
Since we now wait for the inspector window to be visible before navigating to DevTools in the embedded browser (instead of navigating on app start), there could be cases where a notification with a deep link is shown before the navigation happens. This change shows the tool window before trying to navigate and waits for the main URL to be set before navigating to the URL with a widget ID.

![Feb-19-2021 16-55-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6379305/108576711-76b26200-72d3-11eb-896d-d6a3276fd6a4.gif)

comment_data.body: Replacing a completable future with another like this has lead to bugs in the past. A reasonable pattern is to only reset the future if it has not yet completed or to complete the existing future with a failure value depending on what you want to do. Otherwise you can end up with strange behavior if someone was waiting on the future you reset.
you probably want to avoid navigating if the url is null which is what you would probably want to have the future return if the  server was never oppened.
Comment on why you reset the url here.

Okay, we do want to replace the future even if it has completed successfully (since a new URL will have a different vm service URL), but it would make sense to complete with failure if it's not done yet.
no need to log with an error if this is something intentional we are causing if the app got shut.
completing with null since this is a race condition instead of an error we care about.

commit.message: Make inspector visible before updating link
Use completable future URL to avoid race condition
Complete URL future if it's not done, add comment
